# MEMORY.md is a flat list of pointers; per-machine branches will frequently
# add different bullets. The built-in union driver concatenates added lines
# from both sides instead of emitting conflict markers, which is exactly what
# we want during `ucs` rebases. Other memory files (feedback_*.md, etc.) stay
# on the default driver — same-file edits there usually indicate a real
# conflict that should be resolved by hand.
claude/memory/**/MEMORY.md merge=union
